Source: cortex-gpu-amd
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Cortex Linux Team <team@cortexlinux.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://cortexlinux.com
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/cortexlinux/cortex-distro
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/cortexlinux/cortex-distro.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: cortex-gpu-amd
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 cortex-core,
 firmware-amd-graphics
Recommends:
 libdrm-amdgpu1,
 mesa-vulkan-drivers,
 radeontop,
 clinfo
Suggests:
 rocm-hip-runtime,
 rocm-opencl-runtime,
 rocm-smi,
 rocminfo
Provides: cortex-gpu-backend
Description: Cortex Linux AMD GPU enablement
 This meta-package provides AMD GPU support for Cortex Linux,
 including firmware, drivers, and OpenCL runtime.
 .
 Features:
  - AMDGPU kernel driver (in-tree)
  - Mesa Vulkan drivers
  - OpenCL support
  - GPU monitoring (radeontop)
 .
 For ROCm compute support, install cortex-gpu-amd-rocm.

Package: cortex-gpu-amd-rocm
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 cortex-gpu-amd
Recommends:
 rocm-hip-runtime,
 rocm-opencl-runtime,
 rocm-smi,
 rocminfo,
 rocm-cmake,
 hip-runtime-amd
Description: Cortex Linux AMD ROCm compute support
 AMD ROCm runtime for GPU compute on Cortex Linux.
 .
 Includes:
  - HIP runtime for GPU compute
  - ROCm OpenCL runtime
  - ROCm system management (rocm-smi)
 .
 Supported GPU architectures:
  - RDNA3 (MI300)
  - CDNA2 (MI200 series)
  - CDNA (MI100)
  - Vega (MI50, MI60)
